SUPPORT COMMUNICATION - SECURITY BULLETIN

Document ID: c04900820
Version: 1

HPSBGN03523 rev.1 - HP Loadrunner Virtual Table Server, Remote Code Execution

NOTICE: The information in this Security Bulletin should be acted upon as
soon as possible.

Release Date: 2015-11-24
Last Updated: 2015-11-24

Potential Security Impact: Remote Code Execution

Source: Hewlett Packard Enterprise, Product Security Response Team

VULNERABILITY SUMMARY
A potential security vulnerability has been identified in HP Loadrunner
Virtual Table Server that could be exploited remotely resulting in the
execution of code.

References:

CVE-2015-6857
ZDI-CAN-3138

SUPPORTED SOFTWARE VERSIONS*: ONLY impacted versions are listed.
LoadRunner 11.52, 12.00, 12.01, 12.02, 12.50 Virtual Table Server (VTS)

BACKGROUND

CVSS 2.0 Base Metrics
===========================================================
  Reference              Base Vector             Base Score
CVE-2015-6857    (AV:L/AC:L/Au:N/C:C/I:C/A:C)       7.2
===========================================================
             Information on CVSS is documented
            in HP Customer Notice: HPSN-2008-002

RESOLUTION

HP has made the following information available to resolve this vulnerability
for the impacted versions of HP LoadRunner.

Please consult HP Software Support Online (SSO):

https://softwaresupport.hp.com/group/softwaresupport/search-result/-/facetsea
rch/document/KM01936061

